Health Heros will be administering flu shots to students K - 10 on September 30th and to students in 11th & 12th grade on October 8, 2020. If you would like your child to receive the shot, please complete the permission form and return to the school they attend by September 25, 2020. Students will be bringing the form home on September 3rd and 4th or you can download the form here:
https://www.lasd.k12.pa.us/health-services/flu-shots

post_text:
For Immediate Release
Mr. Jeffrey Laux, Athletic Director
lauxj@lasd.k12.pa.us

Update on 2020 Fall Sports Season

Littlestown, PA - The York-Adams Interscholastic Athletic Association met this morning to finalize and update the schedule for the 2020 Fall Sports Season. The updated timeline for practices and contests is as follows:

First Official/Mandatory Practice Dates:

High School Football Heat Acclimatization - August 31

All other sports - September 4

Individual coaches will provide updated practice schedules based on these changes.

First Official Contest Dates:

Golf - September 7

Tennis - September 9

High School Football - September 18

All Other Sports - September 24

The first contest dates are based on PIAA practice requirements for each sport and their mandatory practice start date.

These dates encompass Junior High Sports.

There will be no non-league or scrimmage games played this season.

Stay tuned for updated game schedule information as it is released from the YAIAA.

post_text: Congratulations Justine Garman, ACES Kindergarten Teacher!
shared_text:
WITF
June 8 at 3:00 PM ·

Congratulations to 2020 Teacher Impact Award winner Justine Garman, kindergarten teacher in the Littlestown Area School District!

"She treats all of her students as if they are her own and helps them grow at their own pace. She is incredibly patient and kind!" her nominator told us. "Next, I must say she went above and beyond for my son. She came to his karate class and participated for teacher appreciation week and she also came and watched him during his swimming lessons. This meant so much to him and to me also!"

WITF is proud to partner with Rotary District 7390 to present the Teacher Impact Awards, supported by Franklin & Marshall College.

post_text: Our food service workers go above and beyond! #thunderboltsflyworldclass
shared_text:
Littlestown Area School District Food Service Department
May 19 at 2:45 PM ·

LASD School Lunch Heroes - No need for a Cape when you have an Apron!

The food service ladies have been serving between 150 - 180 bagged lunches each day since the middle of March which must still meet strict government standards. Michelle and Shannon operate the curbside service and Kelli goes on the road to deliver meals to those without transportation. The transportation department has provided a school van which Debbie Evans and Bruce Weaver have stepped up to drive.

When we asked these ladies why they didn’t hesitate to help, the answers were simple. First, and foremost, they love and care about the well-being of their students, and secondly seeing how grateful the families are as they disperse the meals is a reward that makes it all worthwhile.

Thanks to all our everyday heroes out there!

shared_text:
GETTYSBURGTIMES.COM
Cheery Birds project aims to bring smiles, aid nonprofits

Littlestown Area School District
May 10 at 9:10 PM ·

A great opportunity to support the Thunderbolt Foundation is happening right now! The Picket Fence Brigade, an anonymous group of Adams County community members, launched the Cheery Bird project to support non-profit businesses in Adams County that have been negatively impacted by the COVID-19 pandemic. Five hundred wooden birds have been distributed to local businesses, where local residents are encouraged to pick one up for free, decorate it, and post a picture to the Facebook Cheery Birds group, on instagram with #cheerybirds, or email it to picketfencebrigade@gmail.com.
When a picture is posted, include the name of the Thunderbolt Foundation and the Picket Fence Brigade will donate $20 to our non-profit! Birds can be picked up at the Adams County Community Foundation, Blue & Gray Bar and Grill in Gettysburg, Hollabaugh Bros. Market in Biglerville, Ragged Edge Coffee House, Upper Crust, and SCCAP, all in Gettysburg. http://www.gettysburgtimes.com/news/local/article_6e7fcb84-7147-5a06-9011-cc6933716e8a.html

When a picture is posted, include the name of the Thunderbolt Foundation and the Picket Fence Brigade will donate $20 to our non-profit! Birds can be picked up at the Adams County Community Foundation, Blue & Gray Bar and Grill in Gettysburg, Hollabaugh Bros. Market in Biglerville, Ragged Edge Coffee House, Upper Crust, and SCCAP, all in Gettysburg. http://www.gettysburgtimes.com/news/local/article_6e7fcb84-7147-5a06-9011-cc6933716e8a.html
